\int_0^\infty \frac{u^3}{e^u-1} \, du
\pi^4/15
e^u > 1
k > 0
t = ku
 \frac{u^3}{e^u(1 - e^{-u})} = u^3 (e^{-u} + e^{-2u} + e^{-3u} + \ldots)
 \int_0^\infty u^3 e^{-ku} \; du = k^{-4} \int_0^\infty t^3 e^{-t}\; dt = 6 k^{-4}
6 \sum_{k=1}^\infty k^{-4} = 6 \zeta(4) = \pi^4/15
 u \in (0, \infty), 0 < e^{-u} < 1 
 \frac{1}{1 - e^{-u}} = \sum\limits_{k = 0}^\infty e^{-ku} 
 \int\limits_0^\infty u^3 e^{-ku} \ du = \frac{6}{k^4} 
 ku \mapsto x 
 \int\limits_0^\infty x^3 e^{-x} \ dx = 3! = 6 
 \int_0^\infty \frac{e^{-u} u^3}{1 - e^{-u}}\ du = \int_0^\infty \sum_{k = 1}^\infty u^3 e^{-ku} \ du = \sum_{k = 1}^\infty \int_0^\infty u^3e^{-ku} \ du 
 \sum\limits_{k = 1}^\infty \frac{6}{k^4} = 6 \zeta(4) = \frac{\pi^4}{15} 
